    .section-content
      p This page is intended for adults who have completed the three <a href="members/learn">free learn-to-row sessions</a>. Once you have completed your free sessions, you can then join our other adult members and continue your training. 
      p Our adult squad is for anyone no longer in compulsory full-time education; this typically applies to all ages 18+ (specifically, over the age of 18 before the most recent 1st of September at 00:00). 
      p We aim to introduce rowing to everyone, both socially at the club and competitively at local and regional races (please see the <a href="/events">events page</a> for more information on races).
      p Sessions will aim to improve your rowing by mastering your ability to row with others confidently. Once you are able to get into a boat with any other semi-experienced members and consistently row without any major difficulties, you will then be invited to join more on-the-water sessions. Typically sessions will vary between either longer paddles aimed at technical ability and endurance or sprint-based sessions that may challenge both fitness and technical ability in a faster-paced environment.
      p These sessions are split in this way, as the invitation-only sessions can be a lot more challenging for less experienced rowers, and the open-to-all sessions will have a lot more focus on technical ability. This method works to progress each individual in the most well-suited environment possible so that people are not pushed too early, which may subsequently lead to a loss of interest or frustration. Please remember that rowing is like anything else and will take time to master, so don't put too much pressure on yourself. In addition, separating sessions also helps the coaches to manage safety cover and time spent with each crew; having many crews on the water at varying abilities can be very difficult to manage, especially with our ever-expanding community of adults.
      p Invitation-only sessions only apply outside of winter training; during this time all weekday sessions are available to everyone. This is because sessions are moved indoors and become predominantly RowErg based, as it is too dark outside. Session difficulty may still vary per day, but a coach can provide easier sessions or further information as to which days are less challenging and how sessions can be adapted to best suit you.
