    h1 Senior, Masters, and Club Training
    p The senior squad is for those who are experienced in rowing or sculling and who are looking to regularly compete at head races and regattas (further information for head races and regattas can be found on our <a href="/events">events page</a>).
    p Masters is a category for anyone aged 27+ who has experience in rowing or sculling; this is just a specific category of senior used to separate age groups so as not to disadvantage others based on age. However, if you are over the age of 27, you aren't restricted to only racing as a master; the opportunity to race as a senior is still available. British Rowing provides even more information on <a href="https://www.britishrowing.org/go-rowing/types-of-rowing/masters/">Masters Rowing</a>.
    p Club rowing is aimed at any member of the club who just wants to row while possibly enjoying the social interaction provided by all of our members and improving/maintaining fitness.
    p Part of more experienced training includes Saturday and Sunday morning water outings from 8am until 10:30am (however, these training sessions are dependent on both the weather and events) each weekend. Typically these will challenge both fitness and technical ability, building up to racing competitively, and so are invitation only.
    p So, whatever your ability level and whatever your ambition from rowing, you’ll be assured of a very warm and enthusiastic welcome at Sunderland Rowing Club.
  
